## Creating a new custom operator
This feature allows to define a custom operator, that can be used in the data mapping area.

>  Note

A custom operator, also known as user-defined function or operator of operators, is a custom set of operators grouped into a single operator.

The functionality is useful, for example, when you want to define a group of operators that can be reused in multiple points of the data transformation process.

- Open the Mapper resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**ADD OPERATORS**) to add an operator to the mapping area. The **Add operators **panel is displayed on the right.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)	

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Create custom operator**) on the bottom-right to define a personalized function. The **Create User-Defined Function **panel is displayed:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the **Name **text field, enter a name for the new custom operator.

> Important

The name must be unique within the Mapper.

The system allows the use of letters, numbers and the "**_**" (underscore) and "-" (hyphen) characters. It is not allowed to type a number as the first character.

- Select the required option:

**New function**: Create a new, empty function (default option)

- **Import function from file**: Import the function by uploading a previously exported file in the **Attachment **area.

- Click **Create**.

> Tip

Click **Create and edit **to save the new custom operator and be automatically redirected to the configuration editor. For more information, see [Configuring a custom operator](/doxee-platform/docs/1-dt3-mapper-managing-custom-operators#configuring-a-custom-operator) below.

The new custom function is now listed in the operators panel on the righst, under the **Custom Operators **category; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Managing custom operators
- Move your mouse over the name of a custom operator in the operators panel on the right to display the available actions.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu, and select one of the available commands:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download**

Export the custom operator and download it to your local filesystem in XML format.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Permanently delete the custom operator.

> Important

No confirmation is required. This action cannot be undone.

All instances of this operator will also be deleted from the mapping area.

> Note

For more information on how to use and manage operators in the mapping area, see: [DT3 Mapper - Designing Data Transformations in the Mapping Area.](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-mapper-designing-data-transformations-in-the-mapping-area)

## Configuring a custom operator
This feature allows to define the settings of a custom operator. In particular it is possible to:

- Define input and output parameters.

- Connect input and output parameters using the required operators.

- Rename the custom operator.

- Move your mouse over the name of a custom operator in the operators panel on the right to display the available actions.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) The custom operator's configuration editor is displayed; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Define the required input and output parameters, as described in [Defining input and output parameters](#_bookmark46) below.

- Connect input and output parameters using the required built-in operators.

> Important

A custom operator cannot be defined using other custom operators.

> Note

For more information, see: [DT3 Mapper - Designing Data Transformations in the Mapping Area.](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-mapper-designing-data-transformations-in-the-mapping-area)

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) in the top-left to go back to the Mapper's mapping area.

### Available actions
The action icons displayed at the top of the configuration editor allow to perform global actions on the custom operator.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Adding input and output parameters
This feature allows to define the required input and output parameters for a custom operator.

- Access the custom operator's configuration editor, as described in [Configuring a custom operator](/doxee-platform/docs/1-dt3-mapper-managing-custom-operators#configuring-a-custom-operator) above.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add parameter**) on the toolbar at the top. The **Add parameter **panel is displayed.

> Tip

If no parameters have been defined yet, you may also click on the **Add parameter **link at the bottom of the **Input Parameters **and **Output Parameters **panels.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the target structure:

**Input structure**

- **Output structure**

- Select the parameter type and configure the required fields, as described below:

**New custom parameter**: define a custom node with no child elements

![](data:image/png;base64,)

In the **Name **text field, enter a name for the new simple input (or output) parameter.

> Important

The system allows the use of letters, numbers and the "**_**" (underscore) and "-" (hyphen) characters. It is not allowed to type a number as the first character.

- **Import complex parameter**: import an existing hierarchical structure from one of the available schemas, selecting the node root; its child elements will also be imported.

Select the required data structure from the **Structure **list. The **Root element **panel displays the elements of the selected data schema; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the element that you want to use as the **Root element **of the imported tree structure; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Add**. The newly added parameter is displayed in the custom operator's configuration editor; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information on how to connect input and output parameters using the required built-in operators, see: [DT3 Mapper - Designing Data Transformations in the Mapping Area.](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-mapper-designing-data-transformations-in-the-mapping-area)

### Defining the general settings of a custom operator
- Access the custom operator's configuration editor, as described in [Configuring a custom operator](/doxee-platform/docs/1-dt3-mapper-managing-custom-operators#configuring-a-custom-operator) above.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Settings**). The **Settings **panel is displayed on the right; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Name **field, enter the name that you want to assign to the custom operator.

> Important

The system allows the use of letters, numbers and the "**_**" (underscore) and "-" (hyphen) characters. It is not allowed to type a number as the first character.

- *(optional) *In the **Description **field, enter a brief description of the custom operator.

- *(optional) *In the **Grid management **section, select the required options to simplify the view:

**Automatically hide empty columns**

- **Automatically hide empty rows**
